# Commit/trace equivalence program (INVOKE success: multi-RES + near-budget timing)
# Goal:
#   - Exercise S_INV_WAIT close to inv_budget without timing out.
#   - Exercise S_INV_RES with pushes=2.
#   - Validate observable effect by storing results into user RAM and self-checking.
#
# Primitive fid=0x0002 metadata (primtab.hex):
#   pops=0, pushes=2, base_cycles=10 (model=0 => inv_budget=10)
#
# The invoke stub for fid=0x0002 performs:
#   - Multi-cycle wait with two RES writes during S_INV_WAIT
#   - RES[0] = 0xCAFE
#   - RES[1] = 0xBABE
#   - Completion late (near budget) but before timeout
#
# Program:
#   INVOKE 0x0002 => pushes [RES0, RES1] (TOS=RES1)
#   ST [0x82] => store RES1 (0xBABE)
#   ST [0x81] => store RES0 (0xCAFE)
#   Self-check both RAM locations; TRAP on mismatch
#   HALT

# 0: INVOKE fid=0x0002 (A=0x0, B=0x02)
B002
# 1: ST [0x82] (store top = 0xBABE)
3182
# 2: ST [0x81] (store next = 0xCAFE)
3181

# 3: LD [0x81]
3081
# 4: LIT16
6000
# 5: imm expected = 0xCAFE
CAFE
# 6: EQ
1A00
# 7: JNZ +1 (skip TRAP)
4201
# 8: TRAP aux=0x11
F111

# 9: LD [0x82]
3082
# 10: LIT16
6000
# 11: imm expected = 0xBABE
BABE
# 12: EQ
1A00
# 13: JNZ +1
4201
# 14: TRAP aux=0x12
F112

# 15: HALT
F000
